<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-128-446 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 896 510</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  June 17 1991 v8 n24 p2(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FCC clears the final hurdle for ONA tariffing services. (FederalCommunications Commission's new tariffing rules on Open NetworkArchitecture)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Taff, Anita.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Federal Communications Commission's (FCC) decisions ontariffing Open Network Architecture (ONA) services and how tohandle those services under price cap regulations are the lastobstacle for (ONA) and will enable the regional bell holdingcompanies (RBHC) to begin offering those services by 1992.andP;  ONA isa prime factor in the FCC's Third Computer Inquiry, whichspecifies the RBHC entry into enhanced services.andP;  The ONAarchitecture specifies that the RBHC provide customers access tonetworking aspects such as call handling on equal footing withRBHC enhanced services operations.andP;  It also urges RBHC's tounbundle the sale of their services as a means of giving customersthe choice of selecting only the features they want.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Federal Communications CommissionGovernment RegulationTelecommunications ServicesBell Regional Holding CompaniesTariffTelephone Companies.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>